<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 -
        Lubrication and Maintenance - Drain and Replace Oil
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Drain and Replace Oil</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use only SAE Grade 50W oil, Meritor specification O-81, in the transfer case.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Park the vehicle an a level surface. Place a large container under the transfer case.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the magnetic drain plug from the bottom of the transfer case. Drain and discard the
                oil correctly. Clean the plug (Figure 85).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten the drain plug to 35-50 lb-ft (47-69 Nm). Clean the area around the fill
                plug. Remove the fill plug from the transfer case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Add the specified oil until the oil level is even with the bottom of the fill plug hole.
                Install and tighten the fill plug to 35-50 lb-ft (47-68 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Run the vehicle for 1/4 mile (0.4 km). Top off the oil level by adding oil to the fill
                opening. Reinstall and tighten the fill plug to 35-50 lb-ft (47-68 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
